is the lucky girl, follow me.

09:05.295 --> 09:07.833
I'll give you
some vitamin pills and a diet sheet.

09:08.131 --> 09:11.715
Just try not to gain too much weight,
especially in the first three months.

09:12.010 --> 09:13.842
All three of you?

09:15.638 --> 09:19.177
Uh, just out of curiosity,
was it the same guy?

09:19.476 --> 09:23.060
Doctor, we were sent here
by the Catholic Action Committee.

09:23.354 --> 09:25.846
Don't try to con me, honey.
We were given to understand...

09:26.149 --> 09:27.890
That you were desperately
in need of nurses.

09:28.193 --> 09:30.254
That's my problem.
It's got nothing to do with you chicks.

09:30.278 --> 09:32.520
We are the nurses they sent.

09:34.949 --> 09:38.613
I am a psychiatric social worker
with a degree in speech therapy.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.655
Sis... Barbara is
a laboratory technician.

09:41.956 --> 09:45.199
Irene is a R.N.
With a degree in public health.

09:46.336 --> 09:49.170
Great. Just great.

09:50.965 --> 09:54.333
I ask for three hard-nosed nurses
and they send me Park Avenue debutantes.

09:54.636 --> 09:58.175
Which end of Park Avenue do
you figure I'm from, Doctor?

09:58.473 --> 10:02.217
The last three nurses who worked here couldn't take it.
Two of them got raped.

10:02.519 --> 10:06.934
- One even against her will.
- We are very hard-nosed.

10:09.150 --> 10:11.062
Cute.
But not hard enough.

10:11.361 --> 10:13.899
You'll never make it
in this neighborhood, ladies. Never.

10:14.197 --> 10:17.037
Well, Doctor, you don't exactly sound
as if you were born and bred here.

10:17.325 --> 10:21.444
- I'm from Tennessee.
- Obviously not on a diplomatic mission.

10:21.746 --> 10:26.036
Honey, diplomacy starts and ends here
at the point of a switchblade.

10:26.334 --> 10:31.875
- Why don't you go back uptown?
- We are here and we are going to stay here for two months...

10:32.173 --> 10:34.005
which is the length
of our assignment.

10:36.970 --> 10:40.213
Okay. Okay.

10:42.183 --> 10:45.893
- Have you got a place to stay?
- We understand Father Gibbons...

10:46.187 --> 10:49.351
the local parish...
has arranged for an apartment.

10:49.649 --> 10:51.686
Okay. We start work
at 8:00 sharp.

10:51.985 --> 10:54.068
See you then, all right?

10:54.362 --> 10:56.604
All right.

11:01.369 --> 11:04.157
Oh, ladies, what are your names?

11:04.455 --> 11:07.368
Oh, I'm Michelle.

11:07.667 --> 11:10.705
This is Irene and Barbara.

11:11.004 --> 11:13.166
Last names?
Oh.

11:15.175 --> 11:18.464
- You do have last names, don't you?
- Oh, yes.

11:18.761 --> 11:21.720
- It's Gallagher.
- Gallagher.

11:22.015 --> 11:25.508
Nice Irish boy meets pretty French girl
and what happens happens, huh?

11:30.356 --> 11:32.439
Yeah. Barbara?

11:32.734 --> 11:35.693
Bennett.

11:35.987 --> 11:37.944
Irene?
Hawkins.

11:40.283 --> 11:42.946
Okay, ladies, that will be all.
See you tomorrow morning.

11:43.244 --> 11:45.076
Good-bye.

11:48.791 --> 11:51.408
Weirdos, man. Weirdos.

11:51.753 --> 11:54.416
- Just get out of our way.
- Washington Street is our turf, see?

11:54.714 --> 11:58.583
We have no designs on
anything on Washington Street.

11:58.885 --> 12:02.253
Now, if you'll excuse us.

12:19.072 --> 12:21.405
Saints preserve us,
it's a rumble.

12:23.993 --> 12:26.110
There we are.

12:33.086 --> 12:36.625
You get out of here, all of ya!
I'll call the precinct.

12:36.923 --> 12:39.085
Good afternoon.

12:39.384 --> 12:43.253
Talk about the wages of sin.
Will you look at the duds on them.

12:43.554 --> 12:46.922
Oh, we're not what
you think we are.

12:47.225 --> 12:51.811
Sure, and they're calling themselves "massosies" now.
I read it in the Enquirer:

12:52.105 --> 12:55.564
We don't want any monkey business around here,
I'm warning ya.

12:55.858 --> 12:59.522
- We have friends at the precinct.
- We want to be friends too.

12:59.821 --> 13:03.485
Call Father Gibbons.
He'll want to know what's coming into his parish now.

13:08.329 --> 13:10.787
And tell him one of'em's
black as the ace of spades.

13:11.082 --> 13:13.369
Ooh-ooh!

13:18.881 --> 13:20.668
I think our neighbors
are Catholic.

13:20.967 --> 13:23.209
Yes. It's too bad
they're not Christian.

13:44.615 --> 13:49.610
- What a mess.
- What a rotten mess.

13:54.375 --> 13:57.834
Well, furniture would help.

14:00.131 --> 14:04.250
We'll check that out with Father Gibbons
when we go to evening prayers.

14:04.552 --> 14:08.922
In the meantime,
let's get this place next to godliness.

14:25.823 --> 14:29.487
It's only 7:00.
This church keeps banker's hours.

14:37.085 --> 14:40.374
All right.

14:40.671 --> 14:43.914
All right, I'm coming.

14:45.885 --> 14:47.797
I'm coming!

14:52.100 --> 14:53.932
You don't have
to knock the door down.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.395
Father Gibbons?

15:02.693 --> 15:05.356
Come in.
Come in.

15:10.034 --> 15:12.196
Well, what is it?
An accident?

15:12.495 --> 15:16.330
I don't fancy giving a conditional absolution
on a long ride in an ambulance...

15:16.624 --> 15:19.958
And having to pay my own way
back from the hospital in a taxi.

15:20.253 --> 15:22.745
It's nothing like that, Father.
What then?

15:23.047 --> 15:26.006
- We wanted to come into the church to pray.
- Oh.

15:26.300 --> 15:28.212
So it's you?

15:28.511 --> 15:31.845
The secret agents from
the Little Sisters of Mary.

15:32.140 --> 15:35.349
Well, uh, in a manner
of speaking, yes.

15:35.643 --> 15:37.350
You might say
we're on a secret mission.

15:37.645 --> 15:42.606
I don't like underground nuns
who wear bobbed hair and silk stockings.

15:42.900 --> 15:45.358
Oh, but they're nylon, Father.

15:45.653 --> 15:47.986
Thank you.

15:48.281 --> 15:51.069
Father, we're here to help.

15:51.367 --> 15:54.280
For 43 years,
I've managed without you.

15:54.579 --> 15:57.947
The bishop told me to let you
come into the parish and find a place for you to live.

15:58.249 --> 16:00.115
And don't expect
anything else from me.

16:00.418 --> 16:02.284
Well, we'd like to pray.

16:04.505 --> 16:06.588
Very well.

16:12.513 --> 16:15.802
I keep the doors locked.
I'm not about to roll aut the red carpet...

16:16.100 --> 16:19.218
for every thief in the neighborhood to come in
and steal our candlesticks...

16:19.520 --> 16:21.978
and anything else
you can't nail down.

16:22.273 --> 16:26.768
They've already made off with
one of the Stations of the Cross.

16:27.069 --> 16:30.062
Now, when you've finished,
you'll find your own way out.

16:30.364 --> 16:32.356
Thank you, Father.
- Father Gibbons?

16:35.036 --> 16:37.995
May I suggest you put away
the candlesticks...

16:38.289 --> 16:42.829
unlock the doors and make it easier for those
who wish to pray to our Lord?

16:43.127 --> 16:48.748
Flapper skirts on a bride of Christ.
I've been ordered by the bishop to countenance.

16:49.050 --> 16:52.259
But I warn you, Sister,
I'll have none of your arrogant lip.

17:07.818 --> 17:09.605
You think it's twins?

17:09.904 --> 17:13.318
I think it's the Green Bay Packers,
that's what I think it is.

17:15.326 --> 17:17.909
Good morning.
Oh, good morning, ladies.

17:19.704 --> 17:21.696
Back this way, please.

17:21.999 --> 17:24.833
Where's Miss Teenage America?
She gone back to mother already?

17:25.127 --> 17:28.119
The Catholic Action Committee
is sending us some secondhand furniture.

17:28.422 --> 17:31.335
Barbara's gone to wait for it.
She'll be here just as soon as she can.

17:31.634 --> 17:34.342
- It'll be a relief to sleep in a bed again.
- Hmm?

17:34.637 --> 17:37.220
Yeah. You'll take care
of the house calls.

17:37.515 --> 17:40.077
- You'll work with me here in the office all right?
- Yes, Doctor.

17:40.101 --> 17:42.013
Now, about the house calls...

17:42.311 --> 17:45.395
- You probably won't be able to make 'em all in one day.
- I'll make them.

17:47.692 --> 17:51.060
I've shorted you on drugs.
I don't want you getting rolled for narcotics.

17:51.362 --> 17:53.900
Doctor, I was born in a place like this.
I know where it's at.

17:54.198 --> 17:56.030
Fine. Just don't
push your luck, huh?

17:56.325 --> 17:58.567
I got a patient for you.

18:02.081 --> 18:05.290
What's she doing here?
She sure doesn't act like she enjoys it.

18:05.585 --> 18:07.292
She knows it's her duty.

18:07.587 --> 18:10.580
Forcing yourself to like misery?
That's her bag, huh?

18:10.881 --> 18:13.589
A girl like that should get married
and raise a whole bunch of kids.

18:13.884 --> 18:16.342
Turn her hang-ups into
something worthwhile.

18:16.637 --> 18:19.675
In fact, uh, I'd prescribe
that for all three of you.

18:19.974 --> 18:23.308
You said you had a patient.
In my office.

18:25.062 --> 18:27.930
Don't you run off.
I'll be right with you.

18:28.232 --> 18:32.226
Mr. Hernandez, Julio,
this is Miss Gallagher.

18:32.528 --> 18:34.520
How do you do?
Hello.

18:34.822 --> 18:36.609
Stand up.

18:36.907 --> 18:40.696
Miss Gallagher's a speech therapist.
I want her to talk to Julio.

18:40.995 --> 18:44.033
What good is to talk?
He no talk back.

18:45.499 --> 18:49.334
- Julio.
- What's the matter with you?

18:56.260 --> 18:59.970
He's got trouble, miss.
Trouble in school, trouble on the streets...

19:00.264 --> 19:02.301
all because he don't talk good.

19:02.600 --> 19:05.843
Do they have a remedial
speech program at the school?

19:06.145 --> 19:09.138
What school?
He comes from the school with the high wall...

19:09.440 --> 19:13.810
- bars on the window, that kind of school.
- I n-n-no g-g-go back.

19:14.111 --> 19:16.819
You shut up!
You don't talk until you talk good.

19:17.114 --> 19:21.324
- You just listen!
- Julio.

19:21.619 --> 19:23.611
Maybe I can help you.

19:23.913 --> 19:26.075
Maybe we can correct
your speech problem.

19:29.335 --> 19:31.327
W-W-Why...

19:31.629 --> 19:34.793
do I...

19:35.091 --> 19:36.798
do-do it?

19:37.093 --> 19:39.210
T-T-Tell me.

19:41.055 --> 19:43.342
He talk like a dummy,
but he ain't no dummy.

19:43.641 --> 19:45.598
Mr. Hernandez, we're not
gonna get anyplace...

19:45.893 --> 19:48.510
Until you let Julio speak for himself.

19:57.905 --> 19:59.988
Julio.

20:01.325 --> 20:05.114
- That's sharp.
- It feels...

20:06.372 --> 20:08.785
good.

20:09.083 --> 20:11.871
I feel good.

20:15.965 --> 20:18.673
I... talk... better.

20:18.968 --> 20:21.335
Julio, put it down.

20:23.097 --> 20:26.056
You heard the lady.
Drop it or I'll smash your teeth in.

20:26.350 --> 20:28.592
Julio, please,

20:31.689 --> 20:33.726
For me.

20:37.945 --> 20:40.232
You see, he knows
what's good for him.

20:40.531 --> 20:45.777
Julio, I'd like to see you tomorrow afternoon at 4:00.
All right?

20:47.121 --> 20:50.410
Al-All... r-r-right.

20:50.708 --> 20:53.701
- I'll bring him.
- Alone, doctor Carpenter.

20:54.003 --> 20:55.960
Alone, Mr. Hernandez.

21:02.511 --> 21:04.423
Gracias.

21:10.478 --> 21:12.390
It gets a little
messy down here.

21:13.773 --> 21:16.265
I thought you handled that
very well, Miss Gallagher.

21:16.567 --> 21:19.776
Well, you certainly have
a way with a compliment, doctor.

21:20.070 --> 21:23.108
It's Southern charm, we call it.

21:38.047 --> 21:40.380
He seems to be
taking it very well.

21:40.674 --> 21:44.509
Yeah. Well, you don't feel very much
when you're on the stuff.

21:46.597 --> 21:49.681
- "H."
- Oh.

21:55.981 --> 21:57.847
- Hello?
- Hi. Listen, the furniture came...

21:58.150 --> 22:00.062
but the men just
dumped it on the sidewalk...

22:00.361 --> 22:02.273
and drove off before
I could stop them.

22:02.571 --> 22:05.484
Just a minute.
It's Barbara.

22:05.783 --> 22:09.823
The furniture arrived and she needs some help
getting it into the apartment.

22:10.120 --> 22:13.784
Look, I got patients stacked up out there like jet planes
over International Airport.

22:14.083 --> 22:16.416
So I can tell Barbara what
to do with her furniture.

22:16.710 --> 22:20.920
Dr. Carpenter suggests that you rely
on your own resources to solve this problem.

22:47.575 --> 22:50.409
Ay, mama!

23:18.105 --> 23:20.017
Lily.

23:45.883 --> 23:49.672
The hussy.
Massosie.

23:49.970 --> 23:52.633
I have to get this furniture
moved downstairs...

23:52.932 --> 23:56.175
And I need a man.

24:03.442 --> 24:06.401
Oh, good.

24:17.706 --> 24:22.121
All I have is 40 dollars. But I'll get more.
I'll get the other 20.

24:22.419 --> 24:25.457
Now, you borrowed 50, you owe 60,
you pay back 40.

24:25.756 --> 24:28.123
Now you owe 30.

24:28.425 --> 24:30.838
I'll pay it back.
Friday, for sure.

24:31.136 --> 24:34.095
I'm not worried. I got good collateral...
your arms, your legs...

24:34.390 --> 24:36.723
your wife and your kids.

24:45.025 --> 24:47.608
It's very heavy.

24:47.903 --> 24:49.940
You think we're
some kind of faggots?

24:50.239 --> 24:53.528
I beg your pardon?

24:59.206 --> 25:02.324
Everybody says it's
how she was born deaf.

25:13.137 --> 25:16.346
Well, there's no sign of any physical damage.
She doesn't respond.

25:16.640 --> 25:19.007
Has she ever tried to speak?

25:19.309 --> 25:24.179
- I heard her whistle once.
- People learn to whistle by imitating the sound.

25:24.481 --> 25:28.191
- But you got to be able to hear to do that.
- Maybe she can hear.

25:28.485 --> 25:32.695
- Is Amanda your daughter?
- My sister's kid.

25:32.990 --> 25:35.323
She just come and dumped her on me
a couple of years ago.

25:35.617 --> 25:38.701
She-She never wanted the kid
in the first place.

25:38.996 --> 25:42.285
- I think she's autistic.
- Artistic?

25:42.583 --> 25:44.825
Nah. She don't even
lift up a crayon.

25:45.127 --> 25:46.914
No. Autistic.

25:47.212 --> 25:49.750
Sometimes, when a child's
rejected very early in life...

25:50.049 --> 25:53.292
they crawl inside themselves
and shut out the whole world...

25:53.594 --> 25:56.962
as if they're trying to punish the rest of us
along with themselves.

25:59.516 --> 26:02.634
Amanda?

26:04.480 --> 26:07.439
Hey. Hey.

26:07.733 --> 26:11.352
Hey, baby, look at me.
Come on, come on, look at me.

26:11.653 --> 26:14.066
You see how she resists
any kind of contact.

26:14.364 --> 26:16.401
It's typical of
autistic frustration.

26:28.754 --> 26:32.418
Well, she never likes anyone
to pick her up or hold her.

26:32.716 --> 26:35.709
First, I want to make sure
she's not deaf.

26:36.011 --> 26:40.597
- I think she ought to see a specialist.
- You're the doctor.

26:40.891 --> 26:43.652
- Hey, we got it all moved in, chula.
- I don't know how to thank you.

26:43.894 --> 26:46.056
Sure you do.

26:46.355 --> 26:48.688
Hey, we're gonna have a party, huh?
Hey, Tito!

26:48.982 --> 26:51.628
- No, gentlemen, really. I have work to do.
- Hey, you got some wine?

26:51.652 --> 26:55.441
And I will get the first dance.

26:55.739 --> 26:58.231
- No, no. I am the first.
- Oh, no, gentlemen.

26:58.534 --> 27:00.776
- I really think you better go.
- After the party, eh?

27:01.078 --> 27:05.823
- No. No, now, please.
- You heard the lady. Out!

27:08.001 --> 27:10.618
Yeah, sure, we go.

27:23.142 --> 27:24.974
Thank you
very much, sir.

27:25.269 --> 27:28.512
A girl with a shape like yours
can do better than two-bit winos.

27:30.440 --> 27:33.649
I'm The Banker.
Who gave you permission...

27:33.944 --> 27:36.152
to set up shop in my territory?

27:36.446 --> 27:38.108
The Catholic Action Committee.

27:38.407 --> 27:42.947
Well, nowadays, everybody's
got a piece of the action.

27:45.581 --> 27:47.789
Did you stick something
in your eye, Tomas?

27:48.083 --> 27:52.123
- Mm-hmm. Somebody put their fist into his eye.
- Yeah, but I hit him good first.

27:52.421 --> 27:56.040
I don't let nobody
call my sister a dirty, stinking bitch.

27:56.341 --> 27:58.082
She ain't dirty.

27:58.385 --> 28:01.865
Well, you better let Desiree fight her own battles,
because she ain't lost one yet, pal.

28:01.972 --> 28:05.261
Hey, Doc, could I see you a second?
I, uh, have a problem.

28:05.559 --> 28:08.677
Okay. Put two drops
in your eye every four hours.

28:08.979 --> 28:12.063
- And you better put a patch on the champ's eye.
- Yes, Doctor.

28:22.492 --> 28:27.328
- Desiree!
- Oh, Doc. I have such a pain in my left chest.

28:27.623 --> 28:31.333
- Your left chest? Now wait a minute.
- Mm-hmm. A construction.

28:31.627 --> 28:34.665
- A what?
- A construction. I swear it on my mother's grave.

28:34.963 --> 28:37.956
- Your mother's alive.
- So, it could be something serious.

28:43.305 --> 28:46.048
All right. I better not
take any chances.

28:49.978 --> 28:52.561
There?
Um... yeah, right here.

28:57.527 --> 29:01.020
And it hurts when you breathe, right?
Yeah, yeah, it hurts.

29:09.289 --> 29:13.704
- Doc?
- A very interesting case.

29:14.002 --> 29:15.743
Well, what is it?

29:16.046 --> 29:20.882
- You know, you're lucky you came to me when you did.
- Oh, Doc, I was only kidding.

29:21.176 --> 29:24.169
No.

29:24.471 --> 29:28.556
- I don't know how to tell you this, kid.
- But-But...

29:28.850 --> 29:31.433
you've got to do something.
There's nothing I can do.

29:31.728 --> 29:34.088
You mean, I ain't gonna get over it?
Oh, you'll get over it.

29:34.231 --> 29:35.938
Well, what's wrong?

29:36.233 --> 29:40.227
It's called Septum Decimises.
Huh? What's that?

29:40.529 --> 29:43.647
That means that
you're 17 years old.

29:48.036 --> 29:50.278
Uh, Doctor?

29:50.580 --> 29:52.822
Mrs. Rodriguez is here.

29:53.125 --> 29:55.082
Uh, that's all, Camille.

29:56.336 --> 29:58.248
Yeah, for now.

30:02.592 --> 30:04.925
Mm.

30:17.316 --> 30:21.811
- Hello?
- Doctor, I think you better get over here right away.

30:22.112 --> 30:24.104
Yeah. Okay.

30:43.550 --> 30:45.587
You can stop the oxygen, Irene.

30:45.886 --> 30:49.345
- Is she...
- No, she's breathing very well on her own now.

30:49.639 --> 30:51.505
But it was touch-and-go
for a while.

30:53.226 --> 30:57.061
Did you call the ambulance, Michelle?
It's on its way.

30:57.356 --> 31:00.144
Good. You go back
to the clinic with me.

31:00.442 --> 31:02.980
We've done
all we can do here.

31:03.278 --> 31:06.021
Irene, you better stay
until the ambulance gets here.

31:19.711 --> 31:22.704
Hey, Doc.

31:23.006 --> 31:24.622
You call that specialist yet?

31:24.925 --> 31:27.542
He's supposed to get back to me
by the end of the week.

31:40.774 --> 31:43.061
- Miss Parker?
- Yeah?

31:43.360 --> 31:45.560
I want to see Amanda in my office
late Friday afternoon.

31:45.695 --> 31:48.108
Okay?
Whatever you say, Doc.

32:04.339 --> 32:06.251
You bring order and
organization into my life...

32:06.550 --> 32:09.258
and you're gonna ruin everything.
How are things at the hospital?

32:09.553 --> 32:12.671
Oh, just fine.
Miss Kempton goes home today.

32:12.973 --> 32:17.968
Oh. You really saved her life.
You were absolutely wonderful.

32:18.270 --> 32:21.308
You were pretty good yourself,
for a religious fanatic.

32:21.606 --> 32:24.440
Well, I'll, uh...

32:24.734 --> 32:28.023
I'll have Irene put her
on the visiting list for tomorrow, Doctor.

32:28.321 --> 32:30.984
We have a rule around here.
Any nurse that lasts out a full week...

32:31.283 --> 32:33.991
gets to call the doctor by his first name.

32:34.286 --> 32:37.450
Well, I'll try to
remember that... John.

32:37.747 --> 32:40.239
And we celebrate
by having a drink.

32:40.542 --> 32:42.784
Oh, we don't drink.
We don't drink?

32:43.086 --> 32:46.250
Well, uh, wh-what I mean is...

32:46.548 --> 32:48.961
a little wine, occasionally.

32:49.259 --> 32:51.342
We... I...

32:51.636 --> 32:53.923
What I mean is I...
I, uh, don't drink.

32:57.851 --> 33:00.810
Well, if a nurse doesn't drink,
then we usually have dinner.

33:01.104 --> 33:03.687
Yes, I'll bet you do.
But there's no chance.

33:03.982 --> 33:06.770
We're going to try to shame the landlord
into painting the apartment.

33:07.068 --> 33:09.422
You're gonna have to stop
throwing yourself at me like this...

33:09.446 --> 33:12.063
or people will start talking.

33:12.365 --> 33:14.152
Oh, by the way,
you were right about Amanda.

33:14.451 --> 33:17.319
She is autistic, she's not deaf,
'cause I heard her whistle.

33:17.621 --> 33:19.988
Well, I can start working
with her right away.

33:20.290 --> 33:23.499
I'll have to gain her confidence.
Show her love and affection.

33:23.793 --> 33:26.752
There are new techniques
that get results a lot faster.

33:27.047 --> 33:29.835
You mean rage reduction?

33:30.133 --> 33:31.840
I'd rather try patience and love.

33:32.135 --> 33:35.799
I hope we got that much time.
Y-You f-forget me.

33:37.390 --> 33:39.632
No, of course not, Julio.
Just go into the office.

33:39.935 --> 33:41.535
I'll be right with you.
You be all right?

33:41.770 --> 33:44.012
We'll be fine.
It's too bad about dinner.

33:44.314 --> 33:46.397
I was even gonna
pick up the check.

33:50.195 --> 33:53.529
So much?

33:53.823 --> 33:56.190
Oh, that's sheer highway robbery.

33:56.493 --> 33:59.952
- You ought to take out a license to steal, mister.
- Butt out, kid.

34:00.247 --> 34:03.115
You are a walking social injustice.

34:08.045 --> 34:11.585
Every week I try to save money
come Feast of Juan de Cheguez...

34:11.882 --> 34:14.125
so I can buy gifts
for the little ones.

34:14.427 --> 34:16.293
San Juan de Cheguez?

34:16.596 --> 34:18.963
Hey, isn't he the patron saint
of Caribbean fisherman?

34:19.266 --> 34:20.973
Oh, you know him?
Yeah.

34:21.268 --> 34:23.100
Oh, in Puerto Rico,
we have big fiesta...

34:23.395 --> 34:26.058
parade in the streets,
bless the boats.

34:26.356 --> 34:30.690
- Here, they do nothing but try to steal from you.
- You're holding up the line.

34:30.985 --> 34:33.069
Wait a minute.

34:33.362 --> 34:36.356
She gave you a 10 bill dollars.

34:42.621 --> 34:45.034
Oh, gracias.
Muchas gracias, senorita.

34:45.333 --> 34:49.077
- Oh, for the Feast of San Juan de Cheguez.
- Oh, muchas gracias.

34:58.888 --> 35:02.552
Mm.
Noodle ring again, huh?

35:02.851 --> 35:04.843
Mm-hmm.
Noodle ring again.

35:12.444 --> 35:15.357
Got it!
Yeech!

35:17.157 --> 35:19.149
Uh, if you don't like
my noodle ring...

35:19.451 --> 35:22.285
you should have accepted
Dr. Carpenter's invitation to dinner.

35:22.579 --> 35:25.287
I would have.
That'll be five Hail Marys.

35:25.582 --> 35:29.292
Nuns and men don't mix.
Oh, I think he's cute.

35:29.586 --> 35:31.578
- Fifteen.
- Honest. He's groovy.

35:31.880 --> 35:33.712
Twenty-five.

35:36.009 --> 35:37.921
Evening, ladies.
Evening.

35:45.518 --> 35:49.603
Brown paper bags.
I could hear the muscatel bottles rattle.

35:49.898 --> 35:53.642
All right, out of the way,
girls, unless you want to get painted.

35:53.943 --> 35:56.303
Luis, Raoul, start moving the furniture
away from the walls.

35:56.446 --> 35:59.655
Chino, you'll mix the paint.

35:59.949 --> 36:03.488
I know your landlord.
He doesn't shame so easily.

36:45.370 --> 36:47.973
It's too bad Chino and the rest of the boys
couldn't stay for dinner.

36:47.997 --> 36:50.740
Maybe they're not partial
to noodle ring like I am.

36:51.042 --> 36:53.375
Tell me, as a doctor...

36:53.670 --> 36:57.664
would you diagnose what's happening today...
the riots, the student unrest...

36:57.966 --> 37:01.380
as not really the death throes
of an old Order...

37:01.678 --> 37:03.294
But the birth pains of a new one?

37:03.596 --> 37:06.213
- I didn't know I was making a house call.
- Oh, well, I mean...

37:06.516 --> 37:09.554
don't we all, each in our own way,
have to man the barricades?

37:09.853 --> 37:13.688
- At the Ajax Market?
- Um.. If we're all finished?

37:13.982 --> 37:17.191
In the name of the Father,
the Son and the Holy Spirit.

37:17.485 --> 37:19.192
We give Thee thanks,
Almighty God...

37:19.487 --> 37:21.927
for all Thy benefits
which we have received from Thy bounty...

37:22.031 --> 37:23.818
through Christ, our Lord, amen.

37:24.117 --> 37:27.485
In the name of the Father,
the Son and the Holy Spirit.

37:27.787 --> 37:31.701
- I hear it's good for the digestion.
- It is.

37:45.305 --> 37:50.346
"Fiesta San Juan de Cheguez.
August 3, 4:00 to whatever.

37:50.643 --> 37:53.602
Free food, soft drinks.
Support your local patron saint. What is that?

37:53.897 --> 37:57.106
- Well, we're sponsoring it next Saturday.
- I'm against this.

37:57.400 --> 37:59.687
I think we're here
to do a job, not get involved.

37:59.986 --> 38:02.945
Well, I'm for it.
It'll make an awful lot of people very happy.

38:03.239 --> 38:05.572
And happy people
are closer to God.

38:05.867 --> 38:08.701
Look, I don't get it.
What are you, nurses or missionaries?

38:08.995 --> 38:10.861
I think you should
drop the whole thing.

38:11.164 --> 38:14.282
The hospital can't handle
the usual casualties on Saturday night.

38:14.584 --> 38:16.792
Oh, look,
Chino forgot his guitar.

38:17.086 --> 38:19.920
- Won't he need this?
- He could always steal another one.

38:20.215 --> 38:22.423
- Oh.
- Do you think there'll be trouble?

38:22.717 --> 38:24.424
Trouble?
At the fiesta?

38:24.719 --> 38:27.406
You know how it is on a Saturday night down here.
You get everybody together...

38:27.430 --> 38:29.750
blowing out their skulls,
and all the old hates come out...

38:29.933 --> 38:32.013
and you may wind up
with World War III on your hands.

38:32.227 --> 38:34.469
Oh, please don't say that.
It's important to us.

38:35.814 --> 38:37.976
Okay.

38:38.274 --> 38:40.186
Go ahead and have your party
for old Sam Chavez.

38:40.485 --> 38:42.922
But if you really want to get to know
some of the kids around here...

38:42.946 --> 38:45.132
why don't you come down to the park
on a Saturday afternoon...

38:45.156 --> 38:47.318
when we play touch football?
Oh.

38:47.617 --> 38:49.324
Let me show you how to do this.

38:49.619 --> 38:52.612
Put these three fingers
right here, honey. Like that.

38:54.541 --> 38:57.830
Go ahead.

38:58.127 --> 39:01.837
That's right.
Now this one right here.

39:02.131 --> 39:04.839
Very good.
Now these three here.

39:05.134 --> 39:07.501
What?
These three right here.

39:07.804 --> 39:10.342
Now you got a complete
chord change.

39:10.640 --> 39:12.927
Now, see, go back to this one.
Um...

39:13.226 --> 39:16.060
Right.

39:16.354 --> 39:18.186
Now back to this one.

39:19.899 --> 39:22.687
Disgusting movie.

39:22.986 --> 39:25.979
You were right making that
man give us our money back.

39:26.281 --> 39:28.113
When you see
pictures like that...

39:28.408 --> 39:31.697
you realize what a great force
for good Irene Dunne was.

39:37.250 --> 39:39.037
Say, I didn't know
you could do that.

39:39.335 --> 39:41.042
At this hour.

39:41.337 --> 39:44.796
It's got to be an orgy.

39:51.264 --> 39:53.176
Hey, this is fun.

39:53.474 --> 39:57.388
Father Gibbons will certainly
want to hear about this.

40:00.440 --> 40:03.399
I'm not ready.
I'm not ready.

40:18.374 --> 40:22.243
Ah, come on.
Come on.

40:22.545 --> 40:26.505
- That was really terrific.
- Um, give me a hand. Let's get this picture up.

40:26.799 --> 40:30.167
- I'll help.
- That's okay. We can do it ourselves. Thank you.

40:30.470 --> 40:32.553
It's okay.

40:32.847 --> 40:34.964
I'm better
in the kitchen anyway.

40:39.729 --> 40:43.063
What do you know?
We're finally alone.

40:45.818 --> 40:47.901
John, uh, please don't.

40:49.238 --> 40:51.104
I get the feeling
there's a message here.

40:51.407 --> 40:53.273
Like maybe there's somebody else?

40:55.036 --> 40:58.074
You...
you could say that, yes.

40:59.582 --> 41:02.746
Message received.
Good night, Michelle.

41:26.359 --> 41:29.272
Why don't you join
the Y.M.C.A?

41:29.570 --> 41:31.311
You'd save us both
a lot of wear and tear...

41:31.614 --> 41:33.981
if you'd learn to duck
every once in a while, okay?

41:36.369 --> 41:38.486
Okay, Miss Parker.

41:39.622 --> 41:42.581
Come on.
Mandy.

41:42.875 --> 41:47.085
Mandy, come on.

41:47.380 --> 41:49.747
Barbara, take over.
I don't want to be disturbed...

41:50.049 --> 41:51.881
unless it's an emergency.

42:04.063 --> 42:07.397
Do you see that?
Put it right there in that hole.

42:11.237 --> 42:13.775
Come on, darling, take it.

42:14.073 --> 42:17.032
Take it.
Put it in your hand.

42:17.326 --> 42:20.865
That's a girl.
Now put it right...

42:21.164 --> 42:24.999
Ah. Mm-hmm.
Let's try that one more time.

42:25.293 --> 42:27.376
Put it right here.

42:27.670 --> 42:32.916
Come on, put it...
No, no, no. No. Put it...

42:37.055 --> 42:39.388
All right, Amanda,
let's try again.

42:39.682 --> 42:42.049
Put it right... there.

42:47.315 --> 42:50.899
Amanda, put it there.

42:51.194 --> 42:54.904
You can do it. Come on.
You're doing it.

42:55.198 --> 42:57.030
Come on, baby.

42:57.325 --> 43:00.909
Good girl, Amanda.
Very good...

43:01.204 --> 43:04.914
- It's not gonna work, Michelle.
- I don't expect to make too much progress at first.

43:05.208 --> 43:06.949
She's hiding behind
a wall of anger.

43:07.251 --> 43:11.621
It's not gonna work.
I'll take over. We'll try rage reduction.

43:14.509 --> 43:16.546
Take her doll away from her.

43:20.306 --> 43:22.719
No, Amanda.
No more toys, baby.

43:23.017 --> 43:24.724
You got to learn
to start loving people.

43:25.019 --> 43:28.638
I'm gonna hold you till you get rid of all your hate.
Get as mad as you can.

43:28.940 --> 43:31.227
Then you can start
to give love and take love.

43:32.735 --> 43:34.897
Try to get away from me,
baby. Try and get away.

43:35.196 --> 43:37.563
I love you, Amanda.

43:37.865 --> 43:39.982
Don't you like
when people love you?

43:40.284 --> 43:42.364
Come on. I want to see you
get as mad as you can get.

43:42.411 --> 43:44.118
Get all that hate out of you.

43:44.413 --> 43:46.996
Miss Gallagher?

43:47.291 --> 43:49.954
He won't hurt her.

43:50.253 --> 43:52.085
Let's see how mad
you can get, baby.

44:06.519 --> 44:09.808
Oh, um, I'm sorry.
The doctor's tied up right now.

44:11.065 --> 44:13.899
I come back tomorrow.

44:17.655 --> 44:19.567
Get mad.

44:24.203 --> 44:26.286
Come on, let it out.

44:26.581 --> 44:28.493
It's Amanda.

44:28.791 --> 44:31.283
I can take over here.
Why don't you go in and help them?

44:36.382 --> 44:38.374
Okay.

44:40.303 --> 44:43.387
I love you, Amanda.
I love you.

44:49.395 --> 44:52.433
Love you, baby.
Is that as mad as you can get?

44:53.900 --> 44:55.766
Michelle.

44:56.068 --> 44:57.855
Get as mad as you can get.

44:58.154 --> 45:00.862
Hold her feet.

45:01.157 --> 45:03.194
It's okay.
We're not gonna hurt her.

45:03.492 --> 45:05.233
