49:07.153 --> 49:09.987
- Who will kill him?
- The Banker. You don't know how...

49:16.787 --> 49:18.619
You listen to me now.

49:18.914 --> 49:23.249
You fix my ribs,
you give me pills.

49:23.544 --> 49:25.251
This your job.

49:25.546 --> 49:29.460
Anything else,
we all get hurt.

49:35.181 --> 49:37.826
You'll have to keep him in bed.
He cannot go to work in this condition.

49:37.850 --> 49:40.217
He has to.
They will come back for the money on payday.

49:56.702 --> 49:59.285
Cool it.
Junk ain't our bag, sister.

49:59.580 --> 50:03.790
Hey, brother:
She don't want to be our sister.

50:04.084 --> 50:07.122
- If you'll excuse me, I have calls to make.
- They'll wait.

50:07.421 --> 50:09.378
We gotta know where you stand.

50:11.050 --> 50:12.916
I'm a nurse.
That's where I stand.

50:13.219 --> 50:16.212
There's no room down here
for innocent bystanders.

50:16.514 --> 50:19.678
You're either part of the problem
or you're part of the solution.

50:19.975 --> 50:21.762
We've got a feeling
you're neither.

50:22.061 --> 50:25.270
Well, I'm a Negro.
I think that's pretty obvious.

50:25.564 --> 50:30.855
Now where you been, sister?
We ain't Negroes, we're black.

50:31.153 --> 50:34.442
Not her.
She's just been dipped in maple syrup.

50:34.740 --> 50:38.199
You don't talk to me about being black.
I've been black all my life.

50:38.494 --> 50:40.775
- So I don't want to hear that.
- Everything but the soul.

50:40.996 --> 50:44.706
- You copped aut.
